# React Doctor follow-ups (baseline: v0.5.8, after Lit→React migration)

Run `bunx react-doctor --verbose` to re-check. The prop-sync bug
(no-adjust-state-on-prop-change in flight-status) is already fixed. Remaining
findings, triaged — confirm each against the code before acting:

## Maintainability
- Decompose `FFFactionFilterBox` (`src/ui/faction-filter-box.tsx`, ~746 lines) into
  section sub-components — same treatment as the deferred SettingsPanel split.
- `only-export-components`: faction-filter-box exports non-components
  (`getFilterBoxHandle`, `DEFAULT_STATE`) and settings-panel similarly — only hurts
  Fast Refresh, which the userscript build doesn't use. Low priority; consider moving
  helpers to a sibling module if convenient.
- FALSE POSITIVE — `unused-export: default` ×16 on feature modules: the `default`
  exports are consumed by the `import.meta.glob` discovery in `src/features/index.ts`,
  which react-doctor's static analysis can't see. Do not remove.
- FALSE POSITIVE — `unused-dev-dependency: react-doctor`: it's a CLI tool, not imported.

## Bugs (all warnings, behavior currently correct)
- FALSE POSITIVE — `exhaustive-deps` at `src/shims/react.ts:45,50,86`: these are the
  lazy hook *wrapper* functions in the React shim, not real hook call sites.
- `exhaustive-deps` at `faction-filter-box.tsx:318,349`: real mount-only effects with
  intentional empty deps (suppressed via biome-ignore); review if logic changes.
- `no-initialize-state` at `faction-filter-box.tsx:319`: `collapsed` is seeded from the
  mount effect (loadState) rather than useState initializer — causes one extra render.
- `prefer-useReducer` / `no-cascading-set-state`: `flight-status.tsx` and `info-line.tsx`
  have several related useState/setState calls that could be grouped into a reducer.

## Performance
- `rerender-lazy-ref-init` at `faction-filter-box.tsx:164`: `useRef(isMobileView())`
  recomputes every render — use `useRef<…>(null)` + lazy init or `useState(() => …)`.
- `no-inline-exhaustive-style` at `faction-filter-box.tsx:696` + tracked CSS-modules work:
  large inline style objects rebuild each render. Folds into the CSS-modules migration.
- `js-batch-dom-css` at `column-population.ts:246-247,266-267`: batch the sequential
  `element.style.*` writes (cssText / class) to avoid repeated layout.
- `js-set-map-lookups` at `ffscouter.ts:67`, `js-combine-iterations` at `storage.ts:128`,
  `async-await-in-loop` (faction/index.ts:538, index.ts:67/83, dom.ts:384, ffcache.ts:277/293):
  pre-existing non-React hot-path nits; low priority.

## Accessibility
- `control-has-associated-label` ×13 (faction-filter-box checkboxes/inputs, settings-panel):
  add aria-labels to controls whose visible text isn't programmatically associated.
- `no-tiny-text` ×2 (`faction-filter-box.tsx:702`, `info-line.tsx:155`): 11px text; bump to
  ≥12px if it doesn't break the Torn-page layout.

